It's a few hours into the workday when they tell your little group that Miss Hart is ready to brief you on the issue. When you enter the room she's seated with an untouched cup of tea, eyes red-rimmed and puffy and eyebags under her eyes. "Um," she says intelligently when she sees you, and tears start to shine in the corner of her eyes. She presses some tissue to her eyes, sniffling. Clearly a first-timer, and doesn't know how to give a brief...

LEXI HART
Okay... calm... even in the room with all these intimidating presence... she seems to avoid everyone's gaze, looking at the wood grain as she picks nervously at the skin on her hand. She even misses the miscellaneous items that are placed in front of her. She doesn't have an appetite, and seeing the kindness of strangers makes her sob out even more. She doesn't know why they're being so nice to her... get a grip, Lexi, she finds herself saying to her current wreck. "I'm Lexi... Lexi Hart." There's a slight southern drawl to her twang, and she covers her face with a hand, frown deepening as she tries not to have an utter breakdown in a detective agency. "I don't have much, but I told Mr. Quigley I could be put on a payment plan... or something... 's it all of you who're gonna help me find Bailey? I was out all night trying to find him."
THE CASE

"I dunno where they went... no one saw them in the neighborhood, even... last they seen was around the middle school where Bailey goes to. I'm worried sick. What if something bad happened to them?"
